Cope's Murunwa Makwarela has been elected the new speaker of the Tshwane Council. eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Murunwa Makwarela has been elected unopposed as the new speaker of Tshwane. This comes after Katlego Mathebe resigned, to take up the role of Environment and Agriculture Management MMC. WATCH | Council Inaugurations | DA’s Randall Williams elected Tshwane mayor Mathebe has been the speaker since 2016. Watch the video above for more details.